???: —Who's there!? Stay where you are!
Hot Spring Guard: Baa-Baa! It's you again!
Baa Baa: Oh crap, caught red handed...!

Hot Spring Guard: ...Huh?

Baa Baa: If something happens to his women, he'll be pretty angry.

Baa Baa: That's why he's having me do this in secret! He doesn't want anyone to know!
Baa Baa: Like I said, he's a big deal. If anyone finds this out, his reputation'd be ruined!
Baa Baa: ...It's alright! If he takes us both down together, I won't feel so alone~
Hot Spring Guard: Nononono, it's alright, I didn't see anything!
Hot Spring Guard: Just get out of here!
Baa Baa: He's gone. You can come out, princess.
Tindoiimu: I'm surprised you got rid of him so easily.
Tindoiimu: I thought we'd have to fight him.
Baa Baa: Yeah nah, I'm good at dealing with guards.
Baa Baa: Plus, everyone's just looking out for themselves, right? No one's gonna do the right thing if it means making trouble for themselves.
Tindoiimu: ...Is that how you are, too?
Baa Baa: Not if I'm getting paid~
Tindoiimu: Well, then I guess I don't have any reason to worry.
Baa Baa: Hey, of course you don't!
Baa Baa: Alright, we make it out of here and we're outside Hot Spring Street. It's almost light, too, so we should get a move on.
